										<footer class="article-contributor contributors">
									

<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Poe Ballantine</span></strong>&rsquo;s latest book is <em>501 Minutes to Christ</em> (Hawthorne Books). He says he recently drove down the street where he grew up, expecting a flood of memories and emotions. Instead he went right past his old house, not even recognizing the ghost that sat under the laurel tree. He lives in Chadron, Nebraska.</p><a href="/contributors/poe-ballantine" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

							</footer>
						</article>


